        <div class="covid-symptoms">
            <h2>KNOW YOUR SYMPTOMS AND CURE THEM FAST!!</h2>
            <div class="covid_symptns1">
                <p align="justify" class="symptoms">A group of conditions associated with the elevation or lowering of a person's mood, such as depression or bipolar disorder</p>
                <p align="justify"  class="list_1"><b>Most common symptoms:</b></p>
                <ul class="symptons_li">
                    <li>Clinical depression or Major depression. A mental health disorder characterised by persistently depressed mood or loss of interest in activities, causing significant impairment in daily life.Possible causes include a combination of biological, psychological and social sources of distress.</li>
                    <li>Persistent depressive disorder or Dysthymia. A mild but long-term form of depression.Dysthymia is defined as a low mood occurring for at least two years, along with at least two other symptoms of depression.</li>
                    <li>Bipolar disorder or Manic depression A disorder associated with episodes of mood swings ranging from depressive lows to manic highs.</li>
                    <li>Bipolar II disorder A type of bipolar disorder characterised by depressive and hypomanic episodes.It involves at least one depressive episode lasting at least two weeks and at least one hypomanic episode lasting at least four days.</li>
                </ul>
                <p align="justify" class="list_2"><b>Serious symptoms:</b></p>
                <ul class="symptons_li">
                    <li>Clinical Depression:The persistent feeling of sadness or loss of interest that characterises major depression can lead to a range of behavioural and physical symptoms. These may include changes in sleep, appetite, energy level, concentration, daily behaviour or self-esteem. Depression can also be associated with thoughts of suicide.</li>
                    <li>Bipolar disorder: Manic episodes may include symptoms such as high energy, reduced need for sleep and loss of touch with reality. Depressive episodes may include symptoms such as low energy, low motivation and loss of interest in daily activities. Mood episodes last days to months at a time and may also be associated with suicidal thoughts.</li>
                </ul>
                <p align="justify" class="list-info" style="color: rgb(210, 13, 13);"><b>Seek immediate medical attention if you have serious symptoms.  Always call before visiting your doctor or health facility.</b> </p>            

            </div>
